        T
      
    
    {\displaystyle 1/T}
   are not independent. Just using a single such time series, the estimated power spectrum will be very "noisy"; however this can be alleviated if it is possible to evaluate the expected value (in the above equation) using a large (or infinite) number of short-term spectra corresponding to statistical ensembles of realizations of 
  
    
      
        x
        (
        t
        )
      
    
